{
  "stem": "7860.3",
  "chunk_idx": 16,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And like really close, tight to the driver in the street car.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And the German came in with a machine gun, cocked the machine gun right ready to shoot.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And he looked and says, [GERMAN]-- go, keep going.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And he thought I belonged to the street car driver.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "I found myself on the outskirts of Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And I promptly went to a nearby town where I had a bunch of so-called acquaintances-- Polish boys who were stealing coal from the trains with me.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "We used to hop the trains and throw coals off the train heading for Germany.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Which one of my other vocations was.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No idea.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I didn't care.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I still don't care.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't even know what-- if you can tell me now it's the 22nd of October, I wouldn't even know it.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because I'm leaving for Israel.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That's how I know it's the 22nd of October.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I wouldn't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now I know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Approximately.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They look on the calendar and know how much.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That I didn't know.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Day and night, day and night, day and night, day and night.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Five to six years. 1939 to 1945.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I would still continue doing it until these people send me to Lublin.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then I was hitchhiking towards the United States with my friend Chaim Boorstein.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "An adventure we went through, a comic, on our a way to the United States.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We didn't get the United States in one of many other orphanages.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was living with these Polish people.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "These boys who are stealing things, would be selling candies on the train, tending cows.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were a bunch of boys I had some kind of connection.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "One connection to the other one.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the Polish army came in.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And everybody was joyful, they were attacking the tanks, kissing the tanks.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
